# Git Standards

## Conventional Commits (Mandatory)
Format: `{type}({scope}): {short description}`
Types: feat | fix | chore | docs | refactor | test | style
Scopes: backend | frontend | config | deps | graph | api | auth

Examples:
  feat(backend): add ACL pagination to security service
  fix(frontend): correct dagre layout direction for group nodes
  chore(deps): add @xyflow/react and @dagrejs/dagre
  refactor(backend): extract identity resolution into dedicated service

## Branch Strategy (for parallel agent work)
- `main` — always deployable
- `feat/agent-{n}-{feature}` — per-agent feature branch
  - `feat/agent-1-backend-foundation`
  - `feat/agent-2-graph-builder`
  - `feat/agent-3-frontend-canvas`
  - `feat/agent-4-access-trace`
- Merge to main only after agent task is verified

## Never Commit
- `.env` files with real credentials
- `node_modules/` or `bun.lockb` conflicts
- Console.log statements left in production code
- TypeScript errors (`tsc --noEmit` must pass before commit)